  "title": "Security Supervisor",
  "description": "<p><u><strong>Job Responsibilities</strong></u><br /><br />• Perform roving patrols and specific security operations duty assigned by the Assistant Operations Manager or the Operations Manager.<br />• Complete Security team members’ time sheets, rosters, accidents and incident forms.<br />• Conduct security briefing/debriefing.<br />• Perform personnel bearing and equipment checks before deployment for shift<br />• Assist new team members with induction procedures for Security Officers (arrangements for team members ID cards, lockers and uniforms).<br />• Attend to all security incidents promptly and assist in the investigation of incidents and complaints when required.<br />• Recommend the appropriate disciplinary action for Security Service Department’s team members, as required.<br />• Ensure optimum guest service through the delivery of excellent customer service.<br />• Supervise the implementation of emergency procedures as outlined in the relevant Emergency Manual.<br />• Maintain professional skills by staying abreast of current developments and participating in developmental programs available within and outside the company.<br />• Perform other tasks within the IR as directed by the Vice President of Security Service Department or the delegated authority.<br /></p><p><u><strong>Job Requirements</strong></u><br /><br />Education & Certification<br />• Minimum ‘O’ level.<br />• Must have attained at least PRD Security Supervisor Grade. <br />• Must possess a valid Special Employee License during his/her employment.<br /><br />Experience<br />• Preferably with experience with the military/police service/ security industry in a supervisory role.<br />• Good IT skills especially in MS Office.<br /><br />Other Prerequisites<br />• A team player with good interpersonal skills. <br />• Able to work shifts and do overtime.<br />• Able to handle stress and multi-task. <br />• Good written and communication skills.</p>",
